[normal]              
[normal]The position of the staff of the former Irish Bank Resolution Corporation[bold] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Government has received a number of representations on the question of employees of the former Irish Bank Resolution Corporation, which was liquidated by the Irish Government on 7 February 2013.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We fully acknowledge the concerns of those 
[normal]UK
[normal] based employees who face redundancy as a result of this process. As a result of the representations received, 
[normal]the Foreign 
[normal]and Commonwealth 
[normal]Office has discussed this issue 
[normal]with the Irish Government.
[normal] 
[normal]However, whilst the Government is able to pursue requests for clarification, it is important to note that the decision to liquidate the IBRC and the effect this had on employment contracts is a matter for the Irish Government. The Government does not have any jurisdiction in relation to the role currently being played by the Special Liquidators. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](iv)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
